This topic describes how to use SMB Volume Service for Pivotal Platform.

##<a id='using'></a> Using SMB Volume Service for Pivotal Platform

After installation, create the SMB Volume Service with the following options:

1. Provisioning a SMB volume service with these options:
  1. Create an SMB volume service with Azure File Service
    1. [Use an existing storage account on Azure for the volume service](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/smb-volume-release#create-an-smb-volume-service-with-an-existing-storage-account-on-azure)
    1. [Create a new storage account on Azure for the volume service](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/smb-volume-release#create-an-smb-volume-service-with-a-new-storage-account-on-azure)
  1. [Create an SMB volume service with a preexisting share](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/smb-volume-release#create-an-smb-volume-service-with-a-preexisting-share)

1. [Bind the SMB volume service to your application](https://docs.cloudfoundry.org/devguide/services/using-vol-services.html#smb-sample)
